The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited Patriot Industries in Louisa, Virginia to discuss the success of the American economy and the importance of passing the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He praised Patriot Industries for its growth and job creation, attributing it to the policies of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts and deregulation. Pence emphasized the need for Democrats in Congress, particularly those from Virginia, to put politics aside and pass the USMCA, which he claimed would create more jobs and boost the economy. He urged the audience to contact their elected officials and voice their support for the trade agreement. Pence ended his speech by expressing confidence in the future of Virginia and America, citing faith and unity as key factors for success.